replies.bodyText:
@Rachael-E if this is the way forward, then there should be an issue to change up the samples where these are separated to their own files. Since I've started, all the samples using ListCell have had these in their individual files.
I personally think that's the correct way to do it, since essencially ListCell is UI code unrelated to the controller, so putting it in it's own class reduces clutter in the controller and puts the Runtime code in the focus of what's going on there. After all, if we could do this easily, we'd probably do this in the FXML file as well.
Either way, there should at least be a clear guidance in the contribution guidelines, I think

